    "texts": [
        {
            "taxonTextType": "Identification features",
            "shortText": "<p>Large species (largest in the family) with laterally flattened and elongate-oval body, large head and very thick, fleshy lips. The single continuous dorsal fin has 17–18 even spines and 22–24 slightly longer rays. Tailfin large and forked. Pectoral fin with lower 6 rays extended into finger-like projections.</p><p>Body colour plain silvery-grey with slightly darker head and fins. A characteristic red stripe runs from below eye forwards across the forehead.</p>",
            "shortTextKey": "taxon_text_1_3586",
            "longText": null,
            "longTextKey": null,
            "images": []
        },
        {
            "taxonTextType": "Adult size",
            "shortText": "<p>Typically 80 cm but can reach up to 180 cm total length.</p>",
            "shortTextKey": "taxon_text_2_3587",
            "longText": null,
            "longTextKey": null,
            "images": []
        },
        {
            "taxonTextType": "Distribution",
            "shortText": "<p><u>Global:</u> Endemic to southern Africa.</p><p><u>Local/Regional:</u> Namibia to Eastern Cape.</p>",
            "shortTextKey": "taxon_text_3_3588",
            "longText": null,
            "longTextKey": null,
            "images": []
        },
        {
            "taxonTextType": "Biology",
            "shortText": "<p>Usually found singly on deeper rocky reefs, from about 20–150 m depth. Sought after eating fish caught by trawl, as well as by ski-boat fishers and spearfishers.</p>",
            "shortTextKey": "taxon_text_4_3589",
            "longText": null,
            "longTextKey": null,
            "images": []
        },
        {
            "taxonTextType": "Food / prey",
            "shortText": "<p>Feeds during the day on benthic invertebrates, mainly polychaete worms, amphipods and other crustaceans, but also sometimes on small fish and squid.</p>",
            "shortTextKey": "taxon_text_5_3590",
            "longText": null,
            "longTextKey": null,
            "images": []
        },
        {
            "taxonTextType": "Reproduction",
            "shortText": "<p>Reproductive biology of this species has not been studied but other species in this family juveniles are laterally flattened and shelter under floating objects.</p>",
            "shortTextKey": "taxon_text_6_3591",
            "longText": null,
            "longTextKey": null,
            "images": []
        },
        {
            "taxonTextType": "Similar species",
            "shortText": "<p>Thick lips and red stripe in front of the eye are characteristic distinguishing features. The smaller Twotone fingerfin <i>C. brachydactylus</i> is similar in body shape and also has thickened lips, but has a distinctive two-tone brown and white colour pattern after which the name is derived.</p>",
            "shortTextKey": "taxon_text_7_3592",
            "longText": null,
            "longTextKey": null,
            "images": []
        },
        {
